Hey @Huulivoide, thanks for your work putting together this PR. That said, I want to note that keeping the menu open while selecting multiple options is already pretty trivial to implement, as demonstrated in [this example](https://codesandbox.io/s/rbt-keep-menu-open-during-multi-select-nr2y4).

```tsx
const typeaheadRef = useRef(null);

return (
  <Typeahead
    ...
    multiple
    id="keep-menu-open"
    onChange={(selected) => {
      // Keep the menu open when making multiple selections.
      typeaheadRef.current.toggleMenu();
    }}
    ref={typeaheadRef}
  />
);
```

Thanks for the tip. I did end up seeing some weird errors related to `sed`:

```sh
/Users/ericgio/.nvm/nvm.sh: line 1332: 10083 Illegal instruction: 4  sed -e 
            s#/Users/ericgio/.nvm/versions/io.js/#versions/iojs/#;
            s#^/Users/ericgio/.nvm/##;
            \#^[^v]# d;
            \#^versions$# d;
            s#^versions/##;
            s#^v#node/v#;
            \#.*# !d;
           -e s#^\([^/]\{1,\}\)/\(.*\)$#\2.\1#;
/Users/ericgio/.nvm/nvm.sh: line 1340: 10092 Illegal instruction: 4  sed -e s#\(.*\)\.\([^\.]\{1,\}\)$#\2-\1#; -e s#^node-##;
```

After removing just that package, NVM seems to work as expected.

